<subSubSection id="62B19B82FFB6FFFB69F7FA89FCB3FA67" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2A14C809FFB6FFFB69F7FA89FCB3FA67" blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,1436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The key below is based on the comparison of hundreds of specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="EDABB38AFFB6FFFB6AA3FA89FB87FA83" authorityName=": Drake &amp; Poor" authorityYear="1937" box="[963,1120,1374,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Cysteochila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abundantis">
<emphasis id="18DF141BFFB6FFFB6AA3FA89FB87FA83" box="[963,1120,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. abundantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="4E3AB5F8FFB6FFFB69FFFA55FEFDFA67" author="Scott, J." box="[159,282,1410,1436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="289 - 304" refId="ref40256" refString="Scott, J. (1874) On a collection of Hemiptera Heteroptera from Japan. Descriptions of various new genera and species [part 1]. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 4, 14 (82), 289 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937408680968" type="journal article" year="1874">Scott 1874</bibRefCitation>
) and photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="F51076ABFFB6FFFB6B52FA55FD73FA67" box="[562,660,1410,1436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="EDABB38AFFB6FFFB6BD9FA55FCA9FA67" authorityName=": Drake &amp; Ruhoff" authorityYear="1961" box="[697,846,1410,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Cysteochila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrosa">
<emphasis id="18DF141BFFB6FFFB6BD9FA55FCA9FA67" box="[697,846,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. monstrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="62B19B82FFB6FFFB69F7FA10FA7BF98B" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="key">
