<keyLead id="915A6B3CFFB6FFFB69F7FA10FA7BF9EC" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
1 Median spine on head reaching level far remote from bases of frontal spines; outer margin of paranotum gently curved outward in its entire length; anterior margin of hemelytron nearly straight in its entire length; costal area slightly narrower than subcostal area at widest part.......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="EDABB38AFFB6FFFB6D2EF9D5FA7BF9EC" authority="Drake &amp; Poor, 1937" authorityName=": Drake &amp; Poor" authorityYear="1937" box="[1102,1436,1537,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Cysteochila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abundantis">
